---
import SiteLayout from "../../layouts/SiteLayout.astro";
---

<SiteLayout title="Family Law | ImmediateLawyerHelp.com">
 <section class="hero">
    <div class="heroBg" aria-hidden="true"></div>

    <div class="container heroInner">
      <div class="heroCard">
        <h1>Family Law</h1>
        <p class="heroSub">
          Family law issues can affect living arrangements, finances, and parenting plans.
          Choose a topic below, or describe what’s going on to continue.
        </p>

        <form id="heroSearchForm" class="heroSearch" autocomplete="off">
          <input
            id="issueInput"
            type="text"
            placeholder="Briefly describe your situation…"
            aria-label="Describe your situation"
          />
          <button type="submit">Get Started</button>
        </form>

        <div class="heroBadges">
          <span>Confidential</span><span class="sep">•</span>
          <span>Time-sensitive</span><span class="sep">•</span>
          <span>Independent attorneys</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Article -->
  <section class="section sectionTight">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="card">
        <article class="famArticle">
          <h2 class="cardTitle">Common family law matters</h2>
          <p class="muted" style="margin-top:10px; line-height:1.65; max-width:78ch;">
            Family cases often involve court filings, deadlines, and temporary orders that can affect day-to-day life.
            The sections below provide a quick overview and link to dedicated pages (coming soon).
          </p>

          <section class="famSection" id="divorce">
            <h3 class="famH"><a class="famTitleLink" href="/family-law/divorce/">Divorce</a></h3>
            <div class="famImage">
              <img src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1520975693411-6c2b1a2f2b45?auto=format&fit=crop&w=1600&q=60" alt="" loading="lazy" />
            </div>
            <p class="guideMeta famBlurb">
              Divorce often involves decisions about property, debt, support, and future living arrangements.
              Some cases move quickly through agreed terms, while others involve disputes that require hearings and formal discovery.
              Early guidance can help clarify what documents to gather and what steps typically come next.
            </p>
            <a class="famLearn" href="/family-law/divorce/">Learn more →</a>
          </section>

          <section class="famSection" id="child-custody">
            <h3 class="famH"><a class="famTitleLink" href="/family-law/child-custody/">Child Custody</a></h3>
            <div class="famImage">
              <img src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1520975724210-2c6d39b3d0b6?auto=format&fit=crop&w=1600&q=60" alt="" loading="lazy" />
            </div>
            <p class="guideMeta famBlurb">
              Child custody matters can involve parenting schedules, decision-making authority, and transportation logistics.
              Courts may issue temporary orders early, and the outcome can depend on documentation, communication records, and consistency.
              Understanding local standards and timelines can reduce uncertainty.
            </p>
            <a class="famLearn" href="/family-law/child-custody/">Learn more →</a>
          </section>

          <section class="famSection" id="family-law">
            <h3 class="famH"><a class="famTitleLink" href="/family-law/family-law/">Family Law</a></h3>
            <div class="famImage">
              <img src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1521790797524-b2497295b8a0?auto=format&fit=crop&w=1600&q=60" alt="" loading="lazy" />
            </div>
            <p class="guideMeta famBlurb">
              Family law can include support modifications, visitation enforcement, relocation disputes, and related court orders.
              These matters often turn on prior agreements, existing court paperwork, and changes in circumstances.
              A short consultation can help identify what forms or filings may be required.
            </p>
            <a class="famLearn" href="/family-law/family-law/">Learn more →</a>
          </section>
        </article>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Keep sideSearchForm present -->
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container twoCol">
      <div class="card">
        <h2 class="cardTitle">Not sure which applies?</h2>
        <p class="muted" style="line-height:1.6; max-width:72ch;">
          Describe your situation and we’ll route you to the right next step.
        </p>

        <form id="sideSearchForm" class="sideSearch" autocomplete="off">
          <input type="text" placeholder="Describe your issue…" aria-label="Describe your issue" />
          <button type="submit" aria-label="Search">→</button>
        </form>
      </div>

      <aside class="card">
        <h2 class="cardTitle">Notes</h2>
        <ul class="bullets">
          <li>Information on this site is not legal advice.</li>
          <li>Using this site does not create an attorney-client relationship.</li>
          <li>Independent attorneys may have different availability and policies.</li>
        </ul>
      </aside>
    </div>
  </section>

  <style>
    /* Family page-specific styling: restrained images, article rhythm */
    .famArticle .famSection{
      padding: 18px 0 34px;
      border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,.08);
    }
    .famArticle .famSection:last-of-type{
      border-bottom: 0;
      padding-bottom: 10px;
    }
    .famH{
      margin: 0;
      font-size: 18px;
      letter-spacing: -0.01em;
    }
    .famTitleLink{
      text-decoration: none;
    }
    .famTitleLink:hover{
      text-decoration: underline;
    }
    .famImage{
      margin: 12px 0 18px;
      border-radius: 14px;
      overflow: hidden;
      max-width: 62%;
    }
    .famImage img{
      width: 100%;
      height: 140px;
      object-fit: cover;
      display: block;
      filter: saturate(.9) contrast(.95);
    }
    @media (max-width: 900px){
      .famImage{ max-width: 100%; }
    }
    .famBlurb{
      margin-top: 10px;
      line-height: 1.7;
      max-width: 78ch;
    }
    .famLearn{
      display: inline-flex;
      align-items: center;
      gap: 8px;
      margin-top: 12px;
      padding: 10px 12px;
      border-radius: 12px;
      background: rgba(255,255,255,.04);
      border: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,.10);
      text-decoration: none;
      font-weight: 650;
    }
    .famLearn:hover{
      background: rgba(255,255,255,.06);
      border-color: rgba(255,255,255,.14);
      text-decoration: none;
    }
  </style>
</SiteLayout>
